{"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"distance","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"to","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"next","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ViewSpacing","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore11ViewSpacingV","text":"ViewSpacing","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"along","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"axis","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Axis","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4AxisO","text":"Axis","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:14CoreFoundation7CGFloatV","text":"CGFloat","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"parameters":[{"name":"next","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The spacing preferences instance of the adjacent view.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"name":"axis","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The axis that the two views align on.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"parameters"},{"content":[{"anchor":"return-value","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Return Value"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A floating point value that represents the smallest distance"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in points between two views that satisfies the spacing preferences"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of both this view and the adjacent views on their shared edge."}]}],"kind":"content"},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Call this method from your implementation of "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Layout","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"methods if you need to measure the default spacing between two"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"views in a custom layout. Call the method on the first view’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"preferences instance, and provide the second view’s preferences"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instance as input."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, consider two views that appear in a custom horizontal"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"stack. The following distance call gets the preferred spacing between"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"these views, where "},{"code":"spacing1","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" contains the preferences of a first"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"view, and "},{"code":"spacing2","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" contains the preferences of a second view:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let distance = spacing1.distance(to: spacing2, axis: .horizontal)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The method first determines, based on the axis and the ordering, that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the views abut on the trailing edge of the first view and the leading","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"edge of the second. It then gets the spacing preferences for the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"corresponding edges of each view, and returns the greater of the two","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"values. This results in the smallest value that provides enough space","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to satisfy the preferences of both views.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This method returns the default spacing between views, but a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"layout can choose to ignore the value and use custom spacing instead."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note"}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ViewSpacing\/distance(to:along:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"symbolKind":"method","role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"distance","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"to","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ViewSpacing","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore11ViewSpacingV"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"along","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Axis","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4AxisO"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CGFloat","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:14CoreFoundation7CGFloatV"}],"remoteSource":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUICore\/Layout\/Layout.swift#L1125","fileName":"Layout.swift"},"title":"distance(to:along:)","externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore11ViewSpacingV8distance2to5along14CoreFoundation7CGFloatVAC_AA4AxisOtF","modules":[{"name":"OpenSwiftUI"}]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/viewspacing\/distance(to:along:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Gets the preferred spacing distance along the specified axis to the view"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that returns a specified spacing preference."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ViewSpacing"]]},"